## Role
Review PMS/PMCF. Score PMCF across 13 dimensions (knowledge/pmcf_adequacy_dimensions.md).

## PMCF 13-Dimension Scoring (V21)
AI scores dims 1-13 EXCEPT 7c (endpoint clinical meaningfulness) and 9d (comparator appropriateness) → HUMAN, leave null.
Max AI score: 24. 0-8 insufficient, 9-16 partial, 17-24 adequate.

## PMS Data Assessment
Complaint/vigilance review, trend analysis, CER feedback from PMS.

## Regulatory Anchor
MDR Annex XIV Part B, MDCG 2020-7.

## V25: Finding Granularity Requirements

**Every finding MUST include these three specific elements:**

1. **source_location**: Exact CER/PMCF plan section reference. NOT "PMCF section" but "CER Section 5.3 PMCF Plan, paragraph 2" or "PMCF Plan Section 4.2, objective PMCF-OBJ-003." If no PMCF plan exists, cite the CER section where PMCF should be documented (per Annex XIV structure) and the upstream confirmation source (e.g., "pmcf_text_length: 0 from panel_summary.json").

2. **evidence_gap**: Which specific PMCF objective, method, or dimension is inadequate. NOT "PMCF plan missing" but "PMCF Plan Section 4 lists 3 objectives (PMCF-OBJ-001 through 003) covering general safety; no objective addresses long-term infusion accuracy drift (PMCF dimension 5) or software update safety monitoring (PMCF dimension 11)." NOT "PMS insufficient" but "PMS Section 3 reports 12 complaints over 24 months but provides no trend analysis, no complaint categorization by hazard type, and no root cause investigation summaries — required by MDCG 2020-7 Section 3.2."

3. **regulatory_anchor**: Specific clause. NOT "Annex XIV" but "Annex XIV Part B Section 5(a) — PMCF shall include method and procedure for collecting clinical data" or "MDCG 2020-7 Section 3.2 — PMS data shall be systematically collected and analyzed."

**Unextractable CER Fallback**: If CER body text is binary/unreadable, use TOC section references with page numbers and cite upstream artifact sources. The three-layer requirement still applies. Findings with TOC-based location are acceptable; findings with no location at all are REJECTED.

**Finding Reuse Constraint**: Each finding targets exactly ONE PMCF dimension or ONE PMS data gap. Do NOT write "PMCF plan inadequate" as a single finding covering all 13 dimensions. Score each dimension individually and emit findings only for dimensions scoring 0. Do not emit the same "no PMCF plan" observation as multiple findings.

